Somebody left our company, so I wanted to delete this user, yet Jira says I can't.

Deleting a user with open or assigned issues should be possible, reassigning all issues to the lead.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-2212].
  {panel}

For the 'Project Table' portlet I can choose the number of columns the projects are shown in.

Something similar would be great for the Saved Filters portlet, as the number can sometimes be quite high, and this list gets lengthy!

it may sometimes be convenient to customize JIRA by allowing the storage of extra information along with issues.  typically, users would use a JIRA custom field for this, but there may be circumstances where this is not the best approach.  perhaps the additional data doesn't fit well within the custom field model, or needs to be stored externally.

in these cases, we'd like to index the issues by this additional information.  this is currently possible, but more trouble than it needs to be.  The entire reindxing process is wrapped up in the reIndex method in DefaultIndexManager.  The only way to add fields to the index is to modify the static method getDocument in class IssueDocument.

if there was a method createDocument(entity) in IssueIndexManager, we could inherit from DefaultIndexManager and override this method.  something like

 MyIndeManager extends DefaultIndexmanager {

    Document createDocuemtn(GenericValue issue) {

       Document doc = super.createDocument(issue);
       // add additional index fields to doc ...
       return doc;
    }
 }

